cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on automated log analysis to assist practitioners in software operation and maintenance efforts. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a log parsing approach that leverages n-gram dictionaries. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of log parsing, which involves designing and implementing algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as logs are usually stored in databases and the paper discusses the challenges of converting unstructured raw logs into structured data. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses how logs are produced by static templates in the source code (i.e., logging statements) and the challenges of parsing logs when the templates are inaccessible.
